Package: recuse-ssh
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         openssh-server,
         libpam-modules
Description: Recuse cooperative-signal SSH adapter (banner + PAM audit hook)
 Recuse is a cooperative policy channel for AI-agent access — the access-control
 analogue of robots.txt. This package wires the Recuse Signal into OpenSSH on
 Debian/Ubuntu hosts so that conforming automated/LLM-agent clients are told,
 pre-authentication, that automated access is governed here and they should
 recuse themselves.
 .
 It installs:
   * a pre-auth SSH banner (a RECUSE/0.1 sentinel line plus a human-readable
     notice), served via an /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/ drop-in;
   * a PAM session hook (pam_exec) that re-emits a per-session, id-bearing
     notice and appends a JSON audit record to /var/log/recuse/ssh.json;
   * an optional, OFF-by-default behavioral throttle that only ever adds a
     bounded delay (hard-capped at 10s) to rapid repeat connections.
 .
 This is a COOPERATIVE signal, NOT a security control. It announces a policy to
 well-behaved agents; it does not and cannot enforce anything against a
 malicious or non-conforming client. Real security must rest on credentials,
 least privilege, network controls, and bastions.
